8. API Routes
Route	Method	Purpose
/api/field-notes/clusters	GET	Returns all trip-worthy clusters for the authenticated user. Each cluster includes: cluster_id, country_code, region, note_ids, note_count, category_count, duration_estimate, score.
/api/field-notes/clusters/[cluster_id]	GET	Returns full cluster detail: notes with metadata, map coordinates, category breakdown, seasonal analysis, missing categories, budget estimate (if F-6.7.4 active).
/api/field-notes/clusters/[cluster_id]/build	POST	Builds trip from cluster. Body: { selected_note_ids, duration_preference, include_fillers }. Creates trip draft, links notes, creates activity candidates, generates checklist. Returns { trip_id, activities_created, checklist_items_generated }.
/api/field-notes/clusters/[cluster_id]/dismiss	POST	Dismiss cluster prompt. Body: { type: 'not_now' | 'permanent' }. Stores dismissal. Returns { success }.
9. Stress Behavior (§15.0)
Under PROTECTIVE: clustering computation pauses. Existing cluster prompts remain visible but “Build” is disabled. No new trip drafts created automatically.
Stress scenario: 200+ Field Notes across 10 regions. Verify: clustering completes within 3 seconds, correct clusters detected, prompt appears for the strongest cluster only (not all 10 at once).
10. Test Obligations
E2E (tests/e2e/trip-spark.spec.ts):
• Save 5 Field Notes in one region → cluster detected → prompt appears on library page
• Tap Explore → detail view loads with correct items, map, estimates
• Tap Build → trip draft created → navigate to Draft Home → activity candidates present
• Dismiss (not now) → prompt hidden → re-appears after 30 days (mock time)
• Dismiss (permanent) → prompt hidden → does NOT re-appear unless 2+ new notes added
Contract: cluster detection with 3 notes (below threshold) → no prompt. 4 notes same category → no prompt (category diversity required).
11. §9a Dependency Declaration
• Trip workspace: YES — builds trip drafts via ensure_trip_draft_version. Risk: if draft creation fails, show error and keep cluster intact.
• Readiness: YES — fires checklist generation on draft creation. Risk: if checklist generation fails, trip still creates but readiness items are empty.
• Right Now / context: NO
• FOCL / activation: YES — feature_registry entry with hard dependency on F-6.7.2.


